2026-07-20 09:01:22,706 INFO vehicle_advisor.gemini: Gemini response payload (compose_reply): {"reply":"I understand. If your scooty isn't moving even when you try to accelerate after applying the brake, or it feels constantly restricted, it strongly indicates that the brake system is engaged and not fully releasing. This can be caused by a seized brake caliper or wheel cylinder, where the components get stuck and don't retract properly. Alternatively, the master cylinder might not be releasing pressure effectively, or the brake cables could be sticky, preventing the pads or shoes from disengaging fully. This condition needs immediate attention, as it makes your scooty inoperable and poses a safety risk. Our best recommendation is to bring it in so our technicians can quickly diagnose which specific part of your brake system is binding and get it resolved for you.","recommendation_summary":"The scooty's brakes are likely stuck or constantly engaged due to a seized caliper/cylinder, master cylinder issue, or sticky cables. Immediate inspection and repair are required to diagnose and fix the binding component."}
