2026-07-20 09:03:00,462 INFO vehicle_advisor.gemini: Gemini response payload (compose_reply): {"reply":"I understand you're a human being, and it sounds like you're going through a bit of a rough time with your health right now, which I'm sorry to hear. My apologies if my previous responses felt impersonal. My focus is entirely on your vehicle's safety and getting its brake issue resolved. As we discussed, the primary concern for your scooty is still that the brake seems to be constantly engaged, preventing it from moving freely. This usually indicates a mechanical component in the brake system is binding, like a caliper or a cable that isn't releasing properly. It's important to address this to prevent further damage and ensure your safety when you're ready to ride again. Our best recommendation remains to bring your scooty in so our technicians can pinpoint the exact cause of the binding and get it sorted out for you. Is there anything else you've noticed about the scooty's brake issue?","recommendation_summary":"Bring the scooty in for diagnosis and repair of the constantly engaged brake system."}
